olive oil
20 g butter
1.25 cup water (for the rice)
drizzle sesame oil
2 tsp soy sauce
pinch brown sugar
2 egg
2 clove Garlic
1 packet Jasmine rice
1 packet Green beans
1 Carrot
½ bunch Baby Broccoli
1 sachet sesame seeds
1 packet Pork Mince
1 packet Crushed Peanuts
½ packet Hoisin sauce
1 packet Ginger Paste
2 tsp vinegar (rice wine or white wine)
1 tbs water (for the sauce)

• Finely chop garlic.
• In a medium saucepan, melt the butter and a dash of olive oil over a medium heat. Cook garlic until fragrant, 1-2 minutes.
• Add the water (for the rice) and a generous pinch of salt and bring to the boil. Add jasmine rice, stir, cover with a lid and reduce heat to low. Cook for 12 minutes, then remove from heat and keep covered until rice is tender and water is absorbed, 10-15 minutes.

• Meanwhile, trim and halve green beans and baby broccoli (see
ingredients). Thinly slice carrot into sticks.
• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over a medium-high heat. Cook green beans, baby broccoli and carrot until tender, 4-5 minutes.
• Add sesame seeds and a drizzle of sesame oil and cook until fragrant, 30 seconds. Season to taste.
• Transfer veggies to a bowl. Cover to keep warm.

• Return frying pan to a high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. When oil is hot, cook pork mince, breaking up with a spoon, until browned, 3-4 minutes.
• Add crushed peanuts, hoisin sauce (see ingredients), the soy sauce, vinegar, brown sugar, ginger paste and the water (for the sauce) and cook until bubbling, 30 seconds. Transfer to a bowl. Cover to keep warm.
• Wipe out frying pan, then return to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Crack in the eggs and fry until the yolk is cooked to your liking, 4-5 minutes.

• Divide garlic rice and sesame veggies between plates.
• Top with Vietnamese-style pork and peanuts.
• Top with a fried egg to serve. Enjoy!